==English==
===Etymology===
From medieval Latin [[sempiternalis]], from Latin [[sempiternus]], a contraction of [[semperaeternus]], from [[semper]] "always" + [[aeternus]] "eternal".

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /sɛmpɪ'tɜ:nəl/

===Adjective===
{{en-ad|sempiternal}}
#[[everlasting]], [[eternal]] (usually rhetorical)

